Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve any large cauliflower florets.

Pop the @cauliflower florets{300%grams} onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use #scissors{} if easier).

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with 1/2 tsp salt on high heat.

Stir in the @macaroni{180%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

== Sauce ==

Melt the @butter{30%grams} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the butter is hot, stir in the @plain flour{2%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water for the sauce{250%milliliters}, then stir in the @gochujang paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}.

Bring to the boil, lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%grams} into the sauce, then remove from the heat.

Mix in the grated Cheddar until melted.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Stir the roasted cauli, cooked pasta and half the chives into the sauce. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Share the cauliflower mac and cheese between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining chives to finish.

Enjoy!